.TH REGPLAYER 6 "2026-05-09" "v0.1" "Games"
.SH NAME
regplayer \- XMB-inspired media suite for Linux handhelds
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B regplayer
[\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B regplayer
is a media browser and player with an XrossMediaBar-style interface.
It plays music (mp3, flac, ogg, wav, m4a, plus tracker modules and chiptune
formats via libxmp/libgme), videos (via embedded libmpv), and photos.
.PP
By default it scans
.I /userdata/medias
for content. If that path does not exist, it falls back to
.IR ~/Music ", " ~/Videos ", and " ~/Pictures .
Override per-type via Settings > Media Directories.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/regplayer/
Settings, index, history, watched. Defaults to
.IR ~/.config/regplayer .
.TP
.I $XDG_CACHE_HOME/regplayer/thumbnails/
Generated photo + album cover thumbnails (PNG, 120px max edge).
.TP
.I /usr/local/share/regplayer/assets/
Bundled icons, fonts, default wallpaper.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B REG_ASSETS_DIR
Override assets directory (for development).
.SH CONTROLS
Gamepad mapped via SDL3 directly. See on-screen help (X on XMB root).
.SH AUTHOR
REG-Player contributors. Derivative of XMPlayer by Atalay G\(:org\(:un.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mpv (1),
.BR alsamixer (1)
